1. Is JSX mandatory for React?
 A:-No,JSX isn't mandatory in React.React can be written without JSX by using React.createElement().
 Example without JSX:
    const element = React.createElement("h1",null,"Hello world");
 Same with JSX:
    const element = <h1>Hello</h1>;(easier to read,easier to write,looks like html,better for building UI components).

